Share with:
Key Account Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Sales
Industry:
Consumer Goods / FMCG
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
06 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the world’s leading consumer goods and personal care companies. Our respected client is seeking a sales professional, preferably with experience working in a multinational consumer goods or pharmaceutical company, for the job of Key Account Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will report directly to the National Key Account Manager.
Key job responsibilities will include:
Develop and implement the sales strategy per customer in alignment with the Company’s strategic objectives and to manage the customer relationship on an ongoing basis
Responsible for a key customers
The job has accountability for the full scope of company’s commercial interaction with the customer, ranging from the development of sales strategy per customer to the management of promotional activities
The role requires close cross functional interaction with trade marketing, planning, marketing, logistics, finance, and IS
Delivery of   agreed account P&L  as per company objectives
Agree on strategic priority for a customer with the NKAM and develop a full year account master plan in line with sales master plan. The plan should be on the basis of category trend in the account/company brand trend/Nielsen inputs/internal 4P data/Panel data as shared by the Trade Marketing team
Planning  for 4P LSM implementation at the customer level on the basis of insights and learnings drawn from the GSMs
Convert the plans into convincing selling story for the account
Developing annual trading terms to optimizing the cost of business in account and deliver the financial and 4P objectives
Monitoring the performance of initiatives in account master plan against the KPIs, course correcting for deviations
Trade investment to be in line with the plan and to deliver the agreed ROI
Evaluate  the activities and incorporate learnings for bettering the programs in future
Communicate the plans to the field team and take a feedback from the field team on execution
Retain key customers through the development of strong relationships by conducting regular meetings to discuss account performance and to address client concerns and ensure the resolution of issues in a timely manner
Negotiate and close Trading Terms with each and every account on an annual basis
Timely and accurate claim submission from the accounts
Managing and developing company’s position as a key partner/supplier to major customers
Effectively managing/driving company’s presence in highly competitive categories
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in sales, marketing or business administration with a Master’s degree in business administration preferred
At least 5-7 years of mandatory sales experience and key accounts or trade marketing experience in FMCG or pharmaceutical companies
Proven track record in sales management with major retailers
Experience influencing and engaging senior management in own and customer organizations
Results oriented, entrepreneurial and self-motivated
Tenacious and resilient, driven to achieve even when faced with obstacles
Leadership and interpersonal skills capable of building strong working relationships and influencing and customers and internal teams
Strong commercial understanding of business issues and opportunities
Strong understanding of sales and marketing strategy and planning issues
Strong analytical skills with ability to develop strategies, tactics and measurable implementation
Fluent English
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.